The paper deals with the characterization of the diversity-multiplexing tradeoff in a MIMO relay channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of opportunistic scheduling and coding schemes, which are relevant to networking (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also involves communication theory (cs.COMM) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA) in the development of the joint eigenvalue distribution of three mutually correlated random Wishart matrices.
